<li class="commentbody" id="comment-515325">
			<cite><a href='http://www.washingtonmama.blogspot.com' rel='external nofollow' class='url'>Kristin</a></cite>
						&nbsp;
			<a class="commentlink" href="#comment-515325" title="">December 31, 2010</a> 

		
			<div class="commentcount">69</div>

				<p>Yum! I mixed a small batch and it&#8217;s in the freezer now. Looking forward to it&#8230;<br />
A good substitute for egg nog is boiled custard.<br />
6 C milk, 6 egg yolks, 3/4 C sugar, 1 t vanilla. My original directions say to cook the milk then temper the eggs, but I&#8217;ve found that I can just throw the milk eggs and sugar together in a pot and cook on medium stirring constantly until it thickens enough to coat the back of a stainless spoon. Add vanilla and chill. (I&#8217;ve found that I have to strain it through a wire mesh strainer whether or not I temper the eggs).<br />
Tastes like liquid custard and the eggs get cooked, so it&#8217;s a win-win!</p>
	</li>
		
		
		
	
