				<p>This sounds some what familiar to what we call &#8220;lassi&#8221; here in Pakistan. Its heavy and is served at breakfast usually though lassi is made of yoghurt, milk and just the right amount of sugar and then shaked up a bit usually using the traditional hand churner. Milk punch is definitely what I&#8217;d call Lassi if I wanted to translate.</p>
	</li>
		
		
		
	
